{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "# Gmail Email Ingestion via Google Pub/Sub & Apps Script\n\nHere's the full spec rewritten for Gmail, using **Google Pub/Sub push subscriptions** (Gmail's native webhook mechanism) as the backbone instead of Power Automate.\n\n---\n\n## How Gmail \"Webhooks\" Actually Work\n\nGmail doesn't support direct webhooks, but Google provides an official push notification system:\n\n1. **Gmail Watch API** — tells Gmail to monitor an inbox and publish notifications to a Google Pub/Sub topic when new messages arrive\n2. **Google Pub/Sub** — receives those notifications and immediately pushes them to your HTTPS endpoint\n3. **Your backend** — receives the Pub/Sub push, uses the Gmail API to fetch the actual email content, and ingests it\n\nThis is the production-grade approach used by enterprise Gmail integrations. Alternatively, for tenants who prefer a no-code setup, **Google Apps Script** can poll Gmail and POST to your webhook on a time trigger — this is simpler but introduces up to a 1-minute delay.\n\n---\n\n## Webhook Endpoint\n\n**Primary endpoint (Pub/Sub push):**\n```\nPOST /webhooks/email/gmail/:tenantId\n```\n\n**Authentication:** Pub/Sub push requests include a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header issued by Google. Verify this token against Google's token info endpoint (`https://oauth2.googleapis.com/tokeninfo`) to confirm it's a legitimate Pub/Sub push and that the `email` claim matches your registered service account. Additionally, validate a `?token=<secret>` query parameter appended to the subscription push URL during setup as a secondary layer.\n\n**What Pub/Sub delivers:** The push payload is a Pub/Sub message envelope — not the email itself. The `data` field is base64-encoded and contains only the Gmail `historyId` and the user's email address. Your backend must then call the Gmail API to retrieve the actual message.\n\n**Ingestion flow:**\n\n```\nPub/Sub Push → Your endpoint → Decode historyId → Gmail API (history.list) \n→ Gmail API (messages.get) → Parse & store email\n```\n\n**Parse and extract from Gmail API response:**\n- `from` header → sender address\n- `to`, `cc`, `bcc` headers → recipients\n- `subject` header → subject\n- `body.data` (text/plain part) → plain text body\n- `body.data` (text/html part) → HTML body\n- `internalDate` → received timestamp\n- `id` → Gmail message ID (used for deduplication)\n- `threadId` → conversation thread reference\n- `payload.parts` where `filename` is non-empty → attachment metadata (name, MIME type, size, attachment ID)\n\n**HTTP responses:**\n- `200` — success or duplicate (Pub/Sub will not retry on 200)\n- `400` — payload malformed or tenant resolution failed\n- `401` — auth token invalid\n- `500` — internal error (Pub/Sub **will** retry, so only use this when a retry is appropriate)\n\n> **Critical:** Return `200` for duplicates and known-bad messages you've already handled. Returning non-2xx causes Pub/Sub to retry with exponential backoff for up to 7 days.\n\n---\n\n## Database\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE emails (\n  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  tenant_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES tenants(id),\n  gmail_message_id  TEXT NOT NULL,\n  thread_id         TEXT,\n  sender            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  recipients        JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  subject           TEXT,\n  body_plain        TEXT,\n  body_html         TEXT,\n  received_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  attachments       JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  labels            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  raw_payload       JSONB,\n  ingested_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  updated_at        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n\n  CONSTRAINT uq_tenant_gmail_message UNIQUE (tenant_id, gmail_message_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_tenant_id ON emails (tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_received_at ON emails (tenant_id, received_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_sender ON emails (tenant_id, sender);\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- `body_plain` and `body_html` are `TEXT` (unbounded) — avoid `VARCHAR(n)` for email bodies\n- `recipients`, `attachments`, and `labels` use `JSONB` to accommodate variable-length arrays without separate join tables\n- `raw_payload` stores the full Gmail API `Message` object for debugging; consider stripping body content from this field to avoid double-storing large content\n- All queries must include `WHERE tenant_id = $1` as the first filter condition\n\n---\n\n## Gmail OAuth & Watch Setup (Per Tenant)\n\nEach tenant must complete a one-time OAuth authorization before their inbox can be monitored.\n\n**Required Gmail API scopes:**\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly` — to fetch message content\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify` — only if you need to mark messages read or apply labels\n\n**Watch registration** (call this after OAuth completes, and refresh every 7 days — Gmail watch subscriptions expire):\n\n```json\nPOST https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/watch\n{\n  \"topicName\": \"projects/YOUR_PROJECT/topics/gmail-inbound\",\n  \"labelIds\": [\"INBOX\"],\n  \"labelFilterBehavior\": \"INCLUDE\"\n}\n```\n\nStore the returned `historyId` as the tenant's baseline — you'll use this to call `history.list` incrementally so you don't re-process old messages.\n\n**Watch renewal:** Store the `expiration` timestamp from the watch response and set up a daily job to renew watches expiring within 24 hours.\n\n---\n\n## Multi-Tenant Support\n\nTenant resolution uses the `:tenantId` URL path parameter combined with a per-tenant API key stored in your database.\n\n**Tenant record should include:**\n- `gmail_oauth_tokens` (encrypted) — access token, refresh token, expiry\n- `gmail_watch_history_id` — the last processed `historyId` for incremental fetching\n- `gmail_watch_expiration` — when the Pub/Sub watch subscription expires\n- `webhook_api_key` — the secret appended to the Pub/Sub push URL for secondary auth validation\n\n**Isolation guarantees:**\n- All Gmail API calls use the OAuth tokens belonging to the resolved tenant only\n- The `historyId` cursor is stored per-tenant — no shared state\n- All database writes and reads are scoped to `tenant_id`\n- The Pub/Sub topic is shared infrastructure, but tenant identity is resolved from the push URL before any data access occurs\n\n---\n\n## Apps Script Alternative (No-Code Setup)\n\nFor tenants who can't complete OAuth flows or prefer a simpler setup, provide a Google Apps Script template they can deploy themselves:\n\n```javascript\nfunction checkNewEmails() {\n  const webhookUrl = \"https://yourapp.com/webhooks/email/gmail/TENANT_ID\";\n  const apiKey = \"TENANT_API_KEY\";\n  const lastRun = PropertiesService.getScriptProperties()\n                    .getProperty(\"lastRun\") || \"2000/01/01\";\n  \n  const threads = GmailApp.search(`after:${lastRun} in:inbox`);\n  \n  threads.forEach(thread => {\n    thread.getMessages().forEach(msg => {\n      const payload = {\n        messageId: msg.getId(),\n        sender: msg.getFrom(),\n        recipients: msg.getTo(),\n        subject: msg.getSubject(),\n        bodyPlain: msg.getPlainBody(),\n        bodyHtml: msg.getBody(),\n        receivedAt: msg.getDate().toISOString()\n      };\n      \n      UrlFetchApp.fetch(webhookUrl, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"X-API-Key\": apiKey },\n        payload: JSON.stringify(payload),\n        muteHttpExceptions: true\n      });\n    });\n  });\n  \n  PropertiesService.getScriptProperties()\n    .setProperty(\"lastRun\", new Date().toLocaleDateString(\"en-US\"));\n}\n```\n\nTenants set a time-based trigger (every 1 minute) in Apps Script. This approach doesn't require Pub/Sub or OAuth on your backend — the payload arrives pre-parsed, so your endpoint can skip the Gmail API fetch step and ingest directly. The tradeoff is up to a 1-minute delay and reliance on the tenant keeping their Apps Script project active.\n\n---\n\n## Admin Integrations Page — `/admin/integrations`\n\n### Microsoft Gmail / Google Workspace Email Section\n\n**Display prominently at the top:**\n\n```\nYour Webhook URL:\nhttps://yourapp.com/webhooks/email/gmail/[tenant-id]\n\nYour API Key:\n[masked key with copy button]\n```\n\n---\n\n**Setup Option A — Full Integration (Recommended)**\n\nStep-by-step guide in the UI:\n\n1. **Enable the Gmail API** in your Google Cloud project at console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Enable APIs → search \"Gmail API\"\n2. **Create a Pub/Sub topic** named `gmail-inbound` in the same project\n3. **Create a push subscription** pointing to your webhook URL with `?token=YOUR_API_KEY` appended\n4. **Grant publish rights** to `gmail-api-push@system.gserviceaccount.com` on your Pub/Sub topic (this is the Google-managed service account Gmail uses)\n5. **Click \"Connect Gmail Account\"** in this UI — you'll be redirected through Google OAuth to authorize inbox access\n6. **Watch registration happens automatically** after OAuth completes — you'll see a green \"Watching Inbox\" status indicator here once active\n\n---\n\n**Setup Option B — Apps Script (Simpler)**\n\n1. Open [script.google.com](https://script.google.com) while signed into the Gmail account you want to monitor\n2. Create a new project and paste the Apps Script template provided below\n3. Replace `TENANT_ID` and `TENANT_API_KEY` with the values shown above\n4. Click **Run** once manually to grant permissions\n5. Go to **Triggers → Add Trigger** → set `checkNewEmails` to run every 1 minute\n\n---\n\n**Field Mapping Reference (Apps Script option):**\n\n| Your Webhook Field | Apps Script / Gmail Value |\n|---|---|\n| `messageId` | `msg.getId()` |\n| `sender` | `msg.getFrom()` |\n| `recipients` | `msg.getTo()` |\n| `subject` | `msg.getSubject()` |\n| `bodyPlain` | `msg.getPlainBody()` |\n| `bodyHtml` | `msg.getBody()` |\n| `receivedAt` | `msg.getDate().toISOString()` |\n\n---\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n**Duplicate delivery:** The `UNIQUE (tenant_id, gmail_message_id)` constraint is the authoritative deduplication guard. Use an `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` pattern and return `200` either way so Pub/Sub doesn't retry.\n\n**Missing fields:** Subject, plain body, and HTML body should all be nullable at the application layer. Emails with no subject (common for automated senders) or no plain text body (HTML-only emails) are valid and should be stored as-is.\n\n**Large bodies:** Gmail messages can theoretically be very large. Impose a configurable size cap (e.g., 5MB) on `body_html` and `body_plain` before storage, truncating with a metadata flag (`body_truncated: true`) so downstream consumers know the content is incomplete rather than silently missing.\n\n**Expired watch subscriptions:** If a tenant's Gmail watch expires and isn't renewed, Pub/Sub stops receiving notifications silently — no error is thrown. Show an \"Integration Inactive — watch expired\" warning in the UI based on the stored expiration timestamp, and send the tenant an email alert 48 hours before expiry.\n\n**OAuth token refresh:** Access tokens expire every 60 minutes. Always attempt a refresh before making Gmail API calls and update the stored tokens. If a refresh token is revoked (tenant disconnects the app from their Google Account), mark the integration as inactive and alert the tenant.\n\n**historyId gaps:** If your server is down when Pub/Sub delivers a notification, you may miss messages. On reconnection, call `history.list` starting from the last stored `historyId` to backfill any gaps. Cap backfill lookback to 7 days, which is Gmail's history retention window.\n\n**Attachments:** Only store attachment metadata (filename, MIME type, size, Gmail attachment ID) in the database by default. Actual attachment content should be fetched on-demand via the Gmail API using the stored attachment ID, rather than eagerly downloading and storing binary content at ingestion time.",
